Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.85,0:00:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I bring you warm greetings
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.09,0:00:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the United States Bethel family.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.26,0:00:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We want you to know\Nthat we love you all very much,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.80,0:00:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re concerned about you,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.80,0:00:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we pray for you each and every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.07,0:00:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that more and more\Nof you are being affected
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.21,0:00:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,by the coronavirus pandemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.67,0:00:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t go to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.71,0:00:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.81,0:00:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t go to the Kingdom Hall\Nor preach from house to house.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.85,0:00:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you have lost your jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.32,0:00:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have no idea how\Nyou are going to be able to feed your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.19,0:00:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Others have family members who live far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.56,0:00:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no one else in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.16,0:00:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re worried about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.90,0:00:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And sadly, some are mourning\Nthe loss of loved ones
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.97,0:00:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been victims of the disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.17,0:00:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We want you to know\Nthat our hearts ache for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.31,0:00:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so sorry for your loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these are very stressful times,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.88,0:01:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s important to remember one thing:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.92,0:01:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No friend of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.92,0:01:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is ever truly alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.29,0:01:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Through his holy spirit, Jehovah can help us;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.13,0:01:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,he can sustain us\Neven if there’s no one else in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.26,0:01:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Another way Jehovah is helping us
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.80,0:01:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is by means of caring shepherds.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.34,0:01:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is in line\Nwith the promise that he himself made.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.37,0:01:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to read Jeremiah 23:4,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.78,0:01:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll see how this prophecy\Nis being fulfilled today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.41,0:01:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m just going to read a part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.25,0:01:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s the promise Jehovah made:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.82,0:01:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was\Ngoing to “raise up . . . shepherds 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.75,0:01:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who will really shepherd them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.96,0:01:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at the end it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.96,0:01:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“None [of them] will be missing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.20,0:01:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, can you see how that promise
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.53,0:01:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is being fulfilled today in the elders?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.07,0:02:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think of all the work\Nour elders are doing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.74,0:02:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that we don’t miss out\Non spiritual food, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.44,0:02:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They are arranging for us\Nto tie in to congregation meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.91,0:02:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,they set up shepherding calls\Nusing videoconferencing,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.02,0:02:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they arrange for meetings for field service,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and they make sure\Nwe have telephone territory
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.29,0:02:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and letter-writing territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.72,0:02:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, these shepherds
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.76,0:02:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are also concerned\Nabout your physical well-being.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.53,0:02:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So from time to time,\Nthey may also check in on us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.57,0:02:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that we have basic food items,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,medications, and other necessary things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.90,0:02:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If they do that, don’t be shy:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the elders know your needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.44,0:02:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They may also provide practical suggestions\Non how you can protect your health.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.25,0:02:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you can imagine,\Nwhen the pandemic broke out,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.49,0:02:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders had a lot of questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.29,0:02:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They’d never dealt with this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.36,0:02:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly, they needed to do all kinds\Nof things that they hadn’t done before:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.73,0:03:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,set up videoconferencing accounts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,learn how to use new apps like Skype®
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.63,0:03:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and Zoom—what’s that?—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.80,0:03:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and become familiar with how 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.80,0:03:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to organize\Nan entire congregation meeting online.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.98,0:03:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been a huge task for our brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.21,0:03:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want to commend them\Nfor the excellent job they’re doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders had a lot of questions,\Nbut through his organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah provided the direction they needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.36,0:03:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And an experience\Nfrom Canada will bring this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.06,0:03:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch a video\Nin which Brother Warren Shewfelt,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.16,0:03:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a member of the Canada Branch Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.30,0:03:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,explains what happened in Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.07,0:03:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In the face of the coronavirus threat,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.51,0:03:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a body of elders near the Canada branch
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.98,0:03:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,recently met to determine
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,how to go forward with congregation meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.88,0:03:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They had so many questions 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.18,0:03:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,about how to balance\Nthe spiritual needs of the brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.59,0:03:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with government regulations on gatherings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.32,0:04:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They prayed to Jehovah for guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.89,0:04:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But as their meeting went on,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.13,0:04:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it still wasn’t clear to them how to proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.63,0:04:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one of the brothers\Nnoticed on his electronic device
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.87,0:04:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a letter from the branch\Nwith instructions to the elders.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As they read through it,\Nit answered all their questions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.91,0:04:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and even some they hadn’t anticipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.14,0:04:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They viewed this\Nas Jehovah’s answer to their prayers,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.35,0:04:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but now they had\Nless than 24 hours to prepare 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.35,0:04:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,their first-ever congregation meeting\Nby videoconference.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.26,0:04:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayerfully, they followed\Nthe instructions step-by-step,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.96,0:04:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next evening,\Nthe whole congregation gathered
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.33,0:04:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for a meeting by videoconference.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.73,0:04:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The attendance was well over 100 percent,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and one of the families who were \Nin attendance wrote to the elders:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.27,0:04:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“We are so grateful for all the effort 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.44,0:04:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“to provide this\Nmuch needed spiritual food live.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:05:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“It was exactly what we needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.28,0:05:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.69,0:05:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What an encouraging experience that was!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.19,0:05:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Warren.\NWe really appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.69,0:05:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, it reminds me\Nof what the prophet Isaiah foretold
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.80,0:05:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,at Isaiah 65:24:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Even before they call . . . , I will answer; 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.87,0:05:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,while they are yet speaking, I will hear.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.64,0:05:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When we think of caring elders,\Nour circuit overseers come to mind
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.78,0:05:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because they’re often a vital link\Nbetween the branch
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.05,0:05:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the congregation when disaster strikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That reminds me of an experience\Nmy wife and I had back in 2010.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.72,0:05:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was assigned to do\Na shepherding visit to Haiti
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.99,0:05:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,about 10 days after a tremendous earthquake
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.40,0:05:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,took hundreds of thousands of lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.93,0:05:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And sadly, 154 of our brothers\Nalso lost their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I met with the traveling overseers\Nin the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.21,0:06:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I learned that some of them\Nhad lost members of their own family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.31,0:06:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But they were at the forefront\Nof the rescue effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.75,0:06:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so they hadn’t had time\Nto mourn their own loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.42,0:06:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They were still looking\Nfor survivors of the quake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.72,0:06:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did Jehovah say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.29,0:06:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will raise up . . .\Nshepherds who will really shepherd them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.66,0:06:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,None [of them] will be missing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.03,0:06:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And those shepherds in Haiti\Nwere going to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.30,0:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that none of their brothers\Nand sisters were missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.31,0:06:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know that our fine traveling overseers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.61,0:06:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,are continuing to serve congregations
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.81,0:06:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as best they can during this pandemic?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.35,0:06:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In this encouraging video report,\NBrother Paul Echon,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.22,0:06:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who is a member\Nof the Philippines Branch Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.56,0:06:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,tells how even remote congregations\Nare being cared for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.03,0:06:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.20,0:06:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A circuit overseer in the Philippines
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.07,0:07:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote regarding his experience
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.14,0:07:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,using the videoconferencing app Zoom
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to visit two\Nof the remotest congregations in his circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.61,0:07:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Normal travel to these islands by small boat
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.35,0:07:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,may take between five to eight hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.25,0:07:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on sea conditions\Nand the size of waves from the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.02,0:07:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the COVID-19 pandemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.69,0:07:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,travel restrictions to Patnanungan
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.99,0:07:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jomalig islands were implemented.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.89,0:07:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The circuit overseer and his wife
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.26,0:07:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,prayed fervently to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.50,0:07:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for a possible means\Nto still visit the congregations
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.84,0:07:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the last two weeks of March.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.17,0:07:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Just days later, they received\Na letter from the branch office
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.91,0:07:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,about alternative ways\Nof making congregation visits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.85,0:07:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This included\Nthe possibility of virtual visits
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.75,0:07:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with the use of online conferencing tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.09,0:07:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The circuit overseer\Nimmediately informed the elders,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and they excitedly tested\Ntheir newfound means of communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.83,0:07:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The visits were a success!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:08:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers and sisters were so thankful
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and really felt Jehovah’s love for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.57,0:08:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Reflecting on his experience,\Nthe circuit overseer said:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.64,0:08:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is obvious that no coronavirus
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.37,0:08:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“can prevent our Almighty God, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.04,0:08:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“from providing encouragement\Nto his servants today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.35,0:08:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“We are determined more than ever\Nto help and encourage 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.25,0:08:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“the brothers to continue trusting\Nin Jehovah completely,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.02,0:08:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“as mentioned at Psalm 91:2, which says:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.99,0:08:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You are my refuge and my stronghold.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.23,0:08:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we read at Jeremiah 23:4?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.10,0:08:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“None [of them] will be missing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.84,0:08:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knows where all his sheep are,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.97,0:08:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and he arranges for them to be cared for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.58,0:08:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And please give our warm love and greetings
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.18,0:08:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to our brothers in the Philippines.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.91,0:08:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We love them all very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.62,0:08:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do we want to take away\Nfrom this brief discussion?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.69,0:09:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Two points: First, we believe that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.16,0:09:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,will continue to guide his organization\Nevery step of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s been faith-strengthening\Nto see how, at times,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the organization has been\None or even two steps ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the authorities\Nin giving direction to protect the flock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.64,0:09:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s the first point:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.47,0:09:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will continue\Nto direct the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.51,0:09:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, what is one of the means\Nby which he will do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.52,0:09:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,By providing loving shepherds\Nto carry out that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.52,0:09:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And over them is the One who said:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.62,0:09:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am the fine shepherd;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.76,0:09:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“the fine shepherd surrenders his life
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.43,0:09:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in behalf of the sheep.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.70,0:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters,\Ntake good care of yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.54,0:09:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t take chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.90,0:09:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Obey the instructions\Nof “the superior authorities.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We at Bethel are extremely conscientious
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.21,0:09:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about following\Nthe guidelines we’ve received.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.65,0:10:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So if the authorities tell you\Nto stay home, stay home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.42,0:10:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Practice social distancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, keep up-to-date with the news,\Nbut don’t obsess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.06,0:10:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t watch it too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be just too discouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.73,0:10:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what season are we in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.90,0:10:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Memorial season.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.40,0:10:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what should be the real focus\Nof our thoughts at this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.67,0:10:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The incredible gift of the ransom,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.01,0:10:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of Jehovah God,\Nthe love of Christ Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.61,0:10:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Those things should be\Nthe object of our thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.75,0:10:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you feel alone or stressed-out,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.72,0:10:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,repeat to yourself the heart-cheering words
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.22,0:10:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that we find at Hebrews 13:5:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.16,0:10:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will never leave you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.16,0:10:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will never abandon you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.00,0:10:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will never leave you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.97,0:10:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will never abandon you.”
